fix-message.name: Heartbeat
fix-message.description: The Heartbeat monitors the status of the communication link and identifies when the last of a string of messages was not received.

fix-message.name: Test Request
fix-message.description: The test request message forces a heartbeat from the opposing application.

fix-message.name: Resend Request
fix-message.description: The resend request is sent by the receiving application to initiate the retransmission of messages.

fix-message.name: Reject
fix-message.description: The reject message should be issued when a message is received but cannot be properly processed due to a session-level rule violation. A

fix-message.name: Sequence Reset
fix-message.description: The sequence reset message is used by the sending application to reset the incoming sequence number on the opposing side.

fix-message.name: Logout
fix-message.description: Normal termination of the message exchange session will be completed via the exchange of Logout messages.

fix-message.name: Indication
fix-message.description: Indication of interest messages market merchandise which the broker is buying or selling in either a proprietary or agency capacity.

fix-message.name: Advertisement
fix-message.description: Advertisement messages are used to announce completed transactions.

fix-message.name: Execution Report
fix-message.description:
The execution report message is used to:
1. confirm the receipt of an order
2. confirm changes to an existing order (i.e. accept cancel and replace requests)
3. relay order status information
4. relay fill information on working orders
5. reject orders
6. report post-trade fees calculations associated with a trade
NOTE: Execution reports do not replace the end-of-day confirm. Execution reports are to be regarded only as replacements for the existing fill messages currently communicated via telephone.

fix-message.name: Order Cancel Reject
fix-message.description: The order cancel reject message is issued by the broker upon receipt of a cancel request or cancel/replace request message which cannot be honored.

fix-message.name: Logon
fix-message.description: Establishing a FIX connection involves three distinct operations: creation of a telecommunications level link, authentication/acceptance of the initiator by the acceptor and message synchronization (initialization).

fix-message.name: News
fix-message.description: The news message is a general free format message between the broker and institution.

fix-message.name: Email
fix-message.description: The email message is similar to the format and purpose of to the News message, however, it is intended for private use between two par.

fix-message.name: New Order - Single
fix-message.description: The new order message type is used by institutions wishing to electronically submit securities and forex orders to a broker for execution.

fix-message.name: List Order
fix-message.description: The NewOrderList Message can be used in one of two ways depending on which market conventions are being followed.

fix-message.name: Order Cancel Request
fix-message.description: The order cancel request message requests the cancelation of all of the remaining quantity of an existing order. Note that the Order Cancel/Replace Request should be used to partially cancel (reduce) an order).

fix-message.name: Order Replace Request
fix-message.description: The order cancel/replace request is used to change the parameters of an existing order.

fix-message.name: Order Status Request
fix-message.description: The order status request message is used by the institution to generate an order status message back from the broker.

fix-message.name: AllocationInstruction
fix-message.description: The Allocation instruction message provides the ability to specify how an order or set of orders should be subdivided amongst one or more accounts. It can also be used as a confirmation message through which third parties can communicate execution and settlement details between trading partners. In addition, the allocation message can be sent by the broker to communicate fees and other details that can only be computed once the sub-account breakdowns are known.

fix-message.name: List Cancel Request
fix-message.description: The list cancel request message type is used by institutions wishing to cancel previously submitted lists either before or during execution.

fix-message.name: List Execute
fix-message.description: he list execute message type is used by institutions to instruct the broker to begin execution of a previously submitted list. This message may or may not be used, as it may be mirroring a phone conversation.

fix-message.name: List Status Request
fix-message.description: he list status request message type is used by institutions to instruct the broker to generate status messages for a list.

fix-message.name: List Status
fix-message.description: The list status message is issued as the response to a List Status Request message sent in an unsolicited fashion by the sell-side. It indicates the current state of the orders within the list as they exists at the broker s site.

fix-message.name: AllocationInstructionAck
fix-message.description: The Allocation instruction ack message is used to acknowledge the receipt and status of an Allocation Instruction Message.

fix-message.name: DK Trade
fix-message.description: The Don"t Know Trade (DK) message notifies a trading partner that an electronically received execution has been rejected. This message can be thought of as an execution reject message.

fix-message.name: Quote Request
fix-message.description: In some markets it is the practice to request quotes from brokers prior to placement of an order. The quote request message is used for this purpose.

fix-message.name: Quote
fix-message.description: The Quote Message is used as the reponse to a Quote Request message in both indicative, tradeable, and restricted tradeable quoting markets.

fix-message.name: Settlement Instructions
fix-message.description: The Settlement Instructions message provides either the broker's or the institutions instructions for trade settlement

fix-message.name: Market Data Request
fix-message.description: A Market Data Request is a general request for market data on specific securities or forex quotes

fix-message.name: Market Data Snapshot/Refresh
fix-message.description: A Market Data Request is a general request for market data on specific securities or forex quotes

fix-message.name: Market Data Request Reject
fix-message.description: The Market Data Request Reject message is used when the broker cannot honor the Market Data Request, due to business or technical reasons.

fix-message.name: Market Data-Incremental Refresh
fix-message.description: The Market Data message for incremental updates may contain any combination of new changed, or deleted Market Data Entries, for any combination of instruments.

fix-message.name: Quote Cancel
fix-message.description: The Quote Cancel message is used by an originator of quotes to cancel quotes

fix-message.name: Quote Status Request
fix-message.description: The quote status request message is used by the institution to generate an execution report that contains the quote status message back from the counterparty. It is used to retrieve the status of the originating party's quotes and not to obtain market data information.

fix-message.name: Mass Quote Acknowledgement
fix-message.description: An optional response to Quote, MassQuote, Quote Cancel, and Quote Request.

fix-message.name: Security Definition Request
fix-message.description: The Security Definition Request message can be used to request a specific Security, a list of Securities or a list of Security Types that can be traded with the second party.

fix-message.name: Security Status Request
fix-message.description: The Security Status Request message provides for the ability to request the status of a security.

fix-message.name: Security Status
fix-message.description: The Security Status message provides for the ability to report changes in status to a security.

fix-message.name: Trading Session Status Request
fix-message.description: The Trading Session Status Request is used to request information on the status of a market.

fix-message.name: Trading Session Status
fix-message.description: The Trading Session Status provides information on the status of a market.

fix-message.name: Mass Quote
fix-message.description: The Mass Quote message can contain quotes for multiple securites to support applications that allow for the mass quoting of an option series.

fix-message.name: Business Reject
fix-message.description: The Business Message Reject message can reject an application level message which fulfills sesion level rules and cannot be rejected via any other means.

fix-message.name: Bid Request
fix-message.description: The Bid Request message contains bid request(s) based on the Non Disclosed or Disclosed convention.

fix-message.name: Bid Response
fix-message.description: The Bid Response message supply bid(s) based on the Non Disclosed or Disclosed convention.

fix-message.name: List Strike Price
fix-message.description: The Strike Price message is used to exchange strike price information for principal trades.

fix-message.name: Registration Instructions
fix-message.description: The Registration Instructions message type may be used by institutions or retail intermediaries wishing to electronically submit registration information to a broker or fund manager (for CIV) for an order or for an allocations.

fix-message.name: Registration Instructions Response
fix-message.description: The Registration Instructions Response message type may be used by broker or fund manager (for CIV) in response to a Registration Instructions message submitted by an institution or retail intermediary for an order or for an allocation.

fix-message.name: Order Mass Cancel Request
fix-message.description: The order mass cancel request message requests the cancellation of all of the remaining quantity of a group of orders matching criteria specified within the request.

fix-message.name: Order Mass Cancel Report
fix-message.description: The order mass cancel report is used to acknowledge an order mass cancel request. Note that each affected order that is cancelled is acknowledged with a separate Execution Report or Order Cancel Reject Message.

fix-message.name: New Order - Cross
fix-message.description: Used to submit a cross order into a market. The cross order contains two order sides (a buy and a sell). The cross order is identified by its CrossID.

fix-message.name: Cross Order Cancel Replace Request
fix-message.description: Used to modify a cross order previously submitted using the New Order - Cross Message. See Order Cancel Replace Request for details concerning message usage.

fix-message.name: Cross Order Cancel Request
fix-message.description: Used to fully cancel the remaining open quantity of a cross order.

fix-message.name: Security Type Request
fix-message.description: The Security Type Request message is used to return a list of security types available from a counterparty or market.

fix-message.name: Security Types
fix-message.description: The Security Type message is used to return a list of security types available from a counterparty or market.

fix-message.name: Security List Request
fix-message.description: The Security List Request message is used to return a list of securities from the counterparty that match criteria provide on the request.

fix-message.name: Security List
fix-message.description: The Security List message is used to return a list of securities that matches the criteria specified in a Security List Request.

fix-message.name: Derivative Security List Request
fix-message.description: The Derivative Security List Request message is used to return a list of securities from the counterparty that match criteria provided on the request.

fix-message.name: Derivative Security List
fix-message.description: The Derivative Security List message is used to return a list of securities that match the criteria specified in a Derivative Security List Request message.

fix-message.name: Order Multileg
fix-message.description: The new order - multileg is provided to submit orders for securities that are made up of multiple securities, known as legs.

fix-message.name: Multileg Order Cancel Replace Request
fix-message.description: Used to modify a multileg order previously submitted using the New Order - Multileg message. See Order Cancel Replace Request for details concerning message usage.

fix-message.name: Trade Capture Report Request
fix-message.description: Trade Capture Reporting allows sell-side firms to provide timely reporting of completed trades to an external entity not involved in the execution of the trade.

fix-message.name: Trade Capture Report
fix-message.description:
Trade Capture Report message can be: 
 - Used to report trades between counterparties.
 - Used to report trades to a trade matching system.
 - Can be sent unsolicited between counterparties.
 - Sent as a reply to a Treade Capture Report Request.
 - Can be used to report unmatched and matched trades.

fix-message.name: Order Mass Status Request
fix-message.description: The order mass status request message requests the status for orders matching criteria specified within the request.

fix-message.name: Quote Request Reject
fix-message.description: The Quote Request Reject message is used to reject Quote Request messages for all quoting models.

fix-message.name: RFQ Request
fix-message.description: In tradeable and restricted tradeable quoting markets, Quote Requests are issued by counterparties interested in ascertaining the market for an instrument.

fix-message.name: Quote Status Report
fix-message.description:
The quote status report message is used: 
 as the response to a quote status request message. 
 as a response to a quote cancel message. 
 as a response to a quote response message in a negotiation dialog.

fix-message.name: Quote Response
fix-message.description: The Quote Reponse Message is used to repond to a IOI message or Quote message. It is also used to counter a Quote or end a negotiation dialog.

fix-message.name: Confirmation
fix-message.description: The confirmation messages are used to provide individual trade level confirmations from the sell side to the buy side.

fix-message.name: Trade Capture Report Request Ack
fix-message.description: Trade Capture Reporting Request Ack message is used to provide an acknowledgement to a Trade Capture Request message.

fix-message.name: Trade Capture Report Ack
fix-message.description: The Trade Capture Report Ack message can be used to acknowlege trade capture reports received from a counterparty, or used to reject a trade capture report received from a counterparty.

fix-message.name: Allocation Report
fix-message.description: The Allocation report message provides the ability to specify how an order or set of orders should be subdivided amongst one or more accounts. It can also be used as a confirmation message through which third parties can communicate execution and settlement details between trading partners. In addition, the allocation message can be sent by the broker to communicate fees and other details that can only be computed once the sub-account breakdowns are known.

fix-message.name: Allocation Report Ack
fix-message.description: The Allocation report ack message is used to acknowledge the receipt and status of an Allocation Report Message.

fix-message.name: Confirmation Ack
fix-message.description: The confirmation ack (aka Affirmation) message is used to respond to a Confirmation Message.

fix-message.name: Settlement Instruction Request
fix-message.description: The Settlement Instruction Request essage is used to request standing settlement instructions from another party.

fix-message.name: Collateral Request
fix-message.description: An initiator that requires collateral from a respondent sends a Collateral Request. The initiator can be either counterparty to a trade in a two party model or an intermediary such as an ATS or clearinghouse in a three party model. A Collateral Assignment is expected as a response to a request for collateral.

fix-message.name: Collateral Assignment
fix-message.description: Used to assign collateral to cover a trading position. This message can be sent unsolicited or in reply to a Collateral Request message.

fix-message.name: Collateral Response
fix-message.description: Used to respon to a collateral assignment message.

fix-message.name: Collateral Report
fix-message.description: Used to report collateral status when responding to a Collateral Inquiry Message.

fix-message.name: Collateral Inquiry
fix-message.description: Used to inquire for collateral status.

fix-message.name: Network Status Request
fix-message.description: This message is sent immidiately after logging on to inform a network of the type of updates required or to at any other time in the FIX conversation to change the nature of the types of status updates required. It can also be used with a NetworkRequestType of Snapshot to request a one-off report of the status of a network system. Finally this message can also be used to cancel a request to receive updates into the status of the counterparties on a network by sending a NetworkRequestStatusMessage with a NetworkRequestType of StopSubscribing

fix-message.name: Network Status Response
fix-message.description: This message is sent in response to a Network Status Request Message. If the network response payload is larger than the maximum permitted message size for that FIX conversation the response would be several Network Status Response messages the first with a status of full and then as many messages, as updates to the first message, adding information as required

fix-message.name: User Request
fix-message.description: This message is used to initiate a user action, login, logout, or password change. It can also be used to request a report on a user s status.

fix-message.name: User Response
fix-message.description: This message is used to respond to a User Request message, it reports the status of the user after the completion of any action requested in the user request message.

fix-message.name: Collateral Inquiry Ack
fix-message.description:
Used to respond to a Collateral Inquiry in the following situations: 
 - When the CollateralInquiry will result in an out of band response (such as a file transfer). 
 - When the inquiry is otherwise valid but no collateral is found to match the criteria specified on the Collateral Inquiry Message. 
 - When the Collateral Inquiry is invalid based on the business rules of the counterparty.

fix-message.name: Confirmation Request
fix-message.description: The Confirmation Request message is used to request a Confirmatin Message.

fix-tag.name: Account
fix-tag.description: Account mnemonic as agreed between buy and sell sides, e.g. broker and institution or investor/intermediary and fund manager.

fix-tag.name: AdvID
fix-tag.description: Unique identifier of advertisement message.

fix-tag.name: AdvRefID
fix-tag.description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types.

fix-tag.name: AdvSide
fix-tag.description: Broker s side of advertised trade

fix-tag.name: AdvTransType
fix-tag.description: Identifies advertisement message transaction type

fix-tag.name: AvgPx
fix-tag.description: Calculated average price of all fills on this order.

fix-tag.name: BeginSeqNo
fix-tag.description: Message sequence number of first message in range to be resent

fix-tag.name: BeginString
fix-tag.description: Identifies beginning of new message and protocol version. ALWAYS FIRST FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

fix-tag.name: BodyLength
fix-tag.description: Message length, in bytes, forward to the CheckSum field. ALWAYS SECOND FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

fix-tag.name: CheckSum
fix-tag.description: Three byte, simple checksum see Volume 2: Checksum Calculation for description). ALWAYS LAST FIELD IN MESSAGE; i.e. serves, with the trailing SOH, as the end-of-message delimiter. Always defined as three characters. (Always unencrypted)

fix-tag.name: ClOrdID
fix-tag.description: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by the buy-side (institution, broker, intermediary etc.) (identified by SenderCompID or OnBehalfOfCompID as appropriate). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms, particularly those which electronically submit multi-day orders, trade globally or throughout market close periods, should ensure uniqueness across days, for example by embedding a date within the ClOrdID field.

fix-tag.name: Commission
fix-tag.description: Commission. Note if CommType is percentage, Commission of 5 percent should be represented as .05.

fix-tag.name: CommType
fix-tag.description: Commission type

valid-value.name: percentage (for fixed income: Par Value Percentage (aka points))
(for CIV buy orders) percentage waived cash discount
(for CIV buy orders) percentage waived enhanced units

fix-tag.name: CumQty
fix-tag.description: Total quantity (e.g. number of shares) filled.

fix-tag.name: Currency
fix-tag.description: Identifies currency used for price. Absence of this field is interpreted as the default for the security. It is recommended that systems provide the currency value whenever possible. See Appendix 6-A: Valid Currency Codes for information on obtaining valid values.

fix-tag.name: EndSeqNo
fix-tag.description: Message sequence number of last message in range to be resent. If request is for a single message BeginSeqNo = EndSeqNo. If request is for all messages subsequent to a particular message, EndSeqNo = "0" (representing infinity).

fix-tag.name: ExecID
fix-tag.description: Unique identifier of execution message as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN) (will be 0 (zero) forExecType=I (Order Status)).

fix-tag.name: ExecInst
fix-tag.description: Instructions for order handling on exchange trading floor. If more than one instruction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space.

valid-value.name: Percent of volume (indicates that the sender does not want to be all of the volume on the floor vs. a specific percentage)
Reinstate on System Failure (mutually exclusive with Q)
Reinstate on Trading Halt (mutually exclusive with K)
Cancel on Trading Halt (mutually exclusive with L)
Cancel on System Failure (mutually exclusive with H)
Primary peg (primary market - buy at bid/sell at offer)
Fixed Peg to Local best bid or offer at time of order

fix-tag.name: ExecRefID
fix-tag.description: Reference identifier used with Cancel and Correct transaction types.

fix-tag.name: HandlInst
fix-tag.description: Instructions for order handling on Broker trading floor

valid-value.name: Automated execution order, private, no Broker intervention
Automated execution order, public, Broker intervention OK

fix-tag.name: SecurityIDSource
fix-tag.description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityID value. Required if SecurityID is specified.

valid-value.name: Consolidated Tape Association (CTA) Symbol (SIAC CTS/CQS line format)

fix-tag.name: IOIid
fix-tag.description: Unique identifier of IOI message.

fix-tag.name: IOIQltyInd
fix-tag.description: Relative quality of indication

fix-tag.name: IOIRefID
fix-tag.description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE, transaction types.

fix-tag.name: IOIQty
fix-tag.description: Quantity (e.g. number of shares) in numeric form or relative size.

fix-tag.name: IOITransType
fix-tag.description: Identifies IOI message transaction type

fix-tag.name: LastCapacity
fix-tag.description: Broker capacity in order execution

fix-tag.name: LastMkt
fix-tag.description: Market of execution for last fill

fix-tag.name: LastPx
fix-tag.description: Price of this (last) fill.

fix-tag.name: LastQty
fix-tag.description: Quantity (e.g. shares) bought/sold on this (last) fill.

fix-tag.name: LinesOfText
fix-tag.description: Identifies number of lines of text body

fix-tag.name: MsgSeqNum
fix-tag.description: Integer message sequence number.

fix-tag.name: MsgType
fix-tag.description: Defines message type. ALWAYS THIRD FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

valid-value.name: Cross Order Cancel/Replace Request (a.k.a. Cross Order Modification Request)
Multileg Order Cancel/Replace (a.k.a. Multileg Order Modification Request)

fix-tag.name: NewSeqNo
fix-tag.description: New sequence number

fix-tag.name: OrderID
fix-tag.description: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the OrderID field to assure uniqueness across days.

fix-tag.name: OrderQty
fix-tag.description: Quantity ordered. This represents the number of shares for equities or based on normal convention the number of contracts for options, futures, convertible bonds, etc.

fix-tag.name: OrdStatus
fix-tag.description: Identifies current status of order.

valid-value.name: Pending Cancel (e.g. result of Order Cancel Request)
Pending Replace (e.g. result of Order Cancel/Replace Request)

fix-tag.name: OrdType
fix-tag.description: Order type.

valid-value.name: (Limit Day Order with unexecuted portion handled as Market On Close. E.g. Japan)
Market with Leftover as Limit (market order then unexecuted quantity becomes limit order at last price)
Previous Fund Valuation Point (Historic pricing) (for CIV)
Next Fund Valuation Point (Forward pricing) (for CIV)

fix-tag.name: OrigClOrdID
fix-tag.description: ClOrdID of the previous order (NOT the initial order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous order in cancel and cancel/replace requests.

fix-tag.name: OrigTime
fix-tag.description: Time of message origination (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as GMT))

fix-tag.name: PossDupFlag
fix-tag.description: Indicates possible retransmission of message with this sequence number

fix-tag.name: Price
fix-tag.description: Price per unit of quantity (e.g. per share)

fix-tag.name: RefSeqNum
fix-tag.description: Reference message sequence number

fix-tag.name: SecurityID
fix-tag.description: Security identifier value of SecurityIDSource type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires SecurityIDSource.

fix-tag.name: SenderCompID
fix-tag.description: Assigned value used to identify firm sending message.

fix-tag.name: SenderSubID
fix-tag.description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (desk, trader, etc.)

fix-tag.name: SendingTime
fix-tag.description: Time of message transmission (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as GMT)

fix-tag.name: Quantity
fix-tag.description: Overall/total quantity (e.g. number of shares)

fix-tag.name: Side
fix-tag.description: Side of order

valid-value.name: Undisclosed (valid for IOI and List Order messages only)
Cross (orders where counterparty is an exchange, valid for all messages except IOIs)
As Defined (for use with multileg instruments)

fix-tag.name: Symbol
fix-tag.description: Ticker symbol. Common, human understood representation of the security. SecurityID value can be specified if no symbol exists (e.g. non-exchange traded Collective Investment Vehicles)

fix-tag.name: TargetCompID
fix-tag.description: Assigned value used to identify receiving firm.

fix-tag.name: TargetSubID
fix-tag.description: Assigned value used to identify specific individual or unit intended to receive message. ADMIN reserved for administrative messages not intended for a specific user.

fix-tag.name: Text
fix-tag.description: Free format text string

fix-tag.name: TimeInForce
fix-tag.description: Specifies how long the order remains in effect. Absence of this field is interpreted as DAY. NOTE not applicable to CIV Orders.

fix-tag.name: TransactTime
fix-tag.description: Time of execution/order creation (expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as GMT)

fix-tag.name: Urgency
fix-tag.description: Urgency flag

fix-tag.name: ValidUntilTime
fix-tag.description: Indicates expiration time of indication message (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as GMT)

fix-tag.name: SettlType
fix-tag.description: Indicates order settlement period. If present, SettlDate (64) overrides this field. If both SettlType (63) and SettlDate (64) are omitted, the default for SettlType (63) is 0 (Regular)

fix-tag.name: SettlDate
fix-tag.description: Specific date of trade settlement (SettlementDate) in YYYYMMDD format.

fix-tag.name: SymbolSfx
fix-tag.description: Additional information about the security (e.g. preferred, warrants, etc.). Note also see SecurityType (167).

valid-value.name: When Issued for a security to be reissued under an old CUSIP or ISIN
a EUCP with lump-sum interest rather than discount price

fix-tag.name: ListID
fix-tag.description: Unique identifier for list as assigned by institution, used to associate multiple individual orders. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which generate multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ListID field to assure uniqueness across days.

fix-tag.name: ListSeqNo
fix-tag.description: Sequence of individual order within list (i.e. ListSeqNo of TotNoOrds, 2 of 25, 3 of 25, ... )

fix-tag.name: TotNoOrders
fix-tag.description: Total number of list order entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoOrders in each message that has repeating list order entries related to the same ListID. Used to support fragmentation.

fix-tag.name: ListExecInst
fix-tag.description: Free format text message containing list handling and execution instructions.

fix-tag.name: AllocID
fix-tag.description: Unique identifier for allocation message.

fix-tag.name: AllocTransType
fix-tag.description: Identifies allocation transaction type

fix-tag.name: RefAllocID
fix-tag.description: Reference identifier to be used with AllocTransType=Replace or Cancel.

fix-tag.name: NoOrders
fix-tag.description: Indicates number of orders to be combined for average pricing and allocation.

fix-tag.name: AvgPrxPrecision
fix-tag.description: Indicates number of decimal places to be used for average pricing. Absence of this field indicates that default precision arranged by the broker/institution is to be used.

fix-tag.name: TradeDate
fix-tag.description: Indicates date of trade referenced in this message in YYYYMMDD format. Absence of this field indicates current day (expressed in local time at place of trade).

fix-tag.name: PositionEffect
fix-tag.description: Indicates whether the resulting position after a trade should be an opening position or closing position. Used for omnibus accounting - where accounts are held on a gross basis instead of being netted together.

fix-tag.name: NoAllocs
fix-tag.description: Number ofrepeating AllocAccount/AllocPrice entries.

fix-tag.name: AllocAccount
fix-tag.description: Sub-account mnemonic

fix-tag.name: AllocQty
fix-tag.description: Quantity to be allocated to specific sub-account

fix-tag.name: ProcessCode
fix-tag.description: Processing code for sub-account. Absence of this field in AllocAccount / AllocPrice/AllocQty / ProcessCode instance indicates regular trade.

fix-tag.name: NoRpts
fix-tag.description: Total number of reports within series.

fix-tag.name: RptSeq
fix-tag.description: Sequence number of message within report series.

fix-tag.name: CxlQty
fix-tag.description: Total quantity canceled for this order.

fix-tag.name: NoDlvyInst
fix-tag.description: Number of delivery instruction fields in repeating group.

fix-tag.name: AllocStatus
fix-tag.description: Identifies status of allocation.

fix-tag.name: AllocRejCode
fix-tag.description: Identifies reason for rejection.

fix-tag.name: Signature
fix-tag.description: Electronic signature

fix-tag.name: SecureDataLen
fix-tag.description: Length of encrypted message

fix-tag.name: SecureData
fix-tag.description: Actual encrypted data stream

fix-tag.name: SignatureLength
fix-tag.description: Number of bytes in signature field.

fix-tag.name: EmailType
fix-tag.description: Email message type.

fix-tag.name: RawDataLength
fix-tag.description: Number of bytes in raw data field.

fix-tag.name: RawData
fix-tag.description: Unformatted raw data, can include bitmaps, word processor documents, etc.

fix-tag.name: PossResend
fix-tag.description: Indicates that message may contain information that has been sent under another sequence number.

fix-tag.name: EncryptMethod
fix-tag.description: Method of encryption.
